<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[170,795,1530,1683]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,432,1530,1555]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Constantin, 2020" authorityName="Constantin" authorityYear="2020" box="[438,700,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrithorax" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[438,700,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Plectonotum rubrithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[706,791,1530,1555]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is similar to the Peruvian species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Constantin" authorityYear="2020" box="[528,675,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoruficolle" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis box="[528,675,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P.neoruficolle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[679,791,1562,1587]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by the similar habitus and colour pattern. It differs from the latter by the concave frons, broader eyes, longer antennae, narrower pronotal bead and aedeagus shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
